quran[26]{c,v,t}:
  27,56,"The only answer of his people was, \"Drive out Lot and his family from the city. They are a people who make themselves out to be pure"
  27,57,"So We delivered him and his family, except his wife: We ordained her to be one of those who stayed behind"
  27,58,and We pelted them with torrential rain. How dreadful that rain was for those who had been warned
  27,59,"Say, \"All praise be to God, and peace be upon those servants of His whom He has chosen. Is God better, or what they associate with Him"
  27,60,"Who created the heavens and the earth and sends down water for you from the sky, by which We make luxuriant gardens grow, you could never make such trees grow in them, is it another deity besides God? No indeed, but they are a people who equate others with Him"
  27,61,"Who is it that made the earth a stable place to live in? Who made rivers flow through it? Who set mountains upon it and placed a barrier between the two seas? Is there another deity besides God? Indeed, most of them have no knowledge"
  27,62,"Who responds to the oppressed when he calls out to Him, and relieves his suffering and who will make you inheritors of the earth? Then, is there a god besides God? How little you pay heed"
  27,63,"Who guides you in the darkness of the land and sea? Who sends the breezes as heralds of His mercy? Then, is there a deity besides God? Exalted is God above what they associate with Him"
  27,64,"Who originates creation, then regenerates it, and who gives you sustenance from heaven and earth? Then, is there a deity besides God?\" Say, \"Bring forward your proofs, if you are telling the truth"
  27,65,"Say, \"No one in the heavens and the earth has knowledge of the unseen except God.\" They do not know when they will be raised up again"
  27,66,"Indeed, their knowledge of the life to come stops short of the truth: they are [often] in doubt as to its reality: in fact, they are blind to it"
  27,67,"Those who deny the truth say, \"When we have turned to dust like our fathers, shall we be brought back to life again"
  27,68,We and our fathers were promised this before; these are but old stories
  27,69,"Say, \"Roam across the earth and observe what was the end of the sinful ones"
  27,70,"Do not grieve over them, nor feel distressed at their schemes"
  27,71,"They ask, \"When will this promise be fulfilled, if what you say be true"
  27,72,"Say, \"It may be that a part of what you would hasten on is close behind you"
  27,73,"Truly, your Lord is bountiful to mankind, but most of them are not grateful"
  27,74,The Lord knows full well what they conceal in their hearts and what they disclose
  27,75,"there is nothing hidden in heaven and on earth, but is recorded in a clear Book"
  27,76,This Quran explains to the children of Israel much of what they differ over
  27,77,certainly it is guidance and a blessing for the believers
  27,78,"Certainly your Lord will decide between them in His wisdom, He is the Almighty, the All Knowing"
  27,79,so put your trust in God. Surely you are on the path of manifest truth
  27,80,"You cannot make the dead hear, nor can you make the deaf hear your call, when they turn their backs on it"
  27,81,nor can you guide the blind out of their error. You can make only those hear you who believe in Our revelations and surrender themselves to Us